race.comment: ALPHABET (3) resumes having run a strong race on debut at Cranbourne in a handy 2yo maiden back in May, in the market there off a smart trial win but just finding one better. Expecting improvement this time around for the top yard having won another trial leading in. STARBURST (11) is a filly by Magnus on debut for the McEvoy yard. She's had a couple of trials and went well before winning a recent jumpout at Flemington. She should be ready to go for the strong yard. TAUPE (13) has had two starts, hard in the market on debut at Geelong when striking a heavy track before giving a strong sight at Kilmore when run down late. Drawn wide but is quick and can roll forward. If she gets across expect she goes close around here. SET ME LOOSE (10) is three-year-old filly by Hanseatic making her debut. Won a jump-out at Geelong. Respect any support.
